-- India's NSE index breaches 7,000 pts for 1st time
-- By Indulal PM
-- Mon May 12, 2014 04:28AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, May 12 (Reuters) - India's NSE index gained as much as much as 2.1 percent to breach the psychologically key level of 7,000 points for the first time on hopes that exit polls would show Bharatiya Janata Party and its allies winning a majority in ongoing elections.

The broader NSE's <.NSEI> record high of 7,000.25 points breached an all-time high of 6,871.35 hit just on Friday.